== WHAT IS THIS ==

These python scripts will generate setup time graphics
from the TalkPlus CDR stats.

The cdr-get-callid.py script is a convenience script for
retrieving a single call ids full json stats.

== INSTALLATION ==
 $ sudo apt-get install python-pymongo python-pandas

Move these python files into the correct directory.
 $ sudo mkdir -p /usr/share/cdr_stats/templates/frontend/comoyo
 $ sudo cp cdr-setup-times.py /usr/share/cdr_stats/templates/frontend/comoyo

If you are running an older ubuntu distribution, check the source files for
changing the MongoClient() call to a Connection() call used by earlier
versions fo the pymongo plugin.

Create the following script in /etc/cron.hourly/cdr-hourly
----------------------------------------------
#!/bin/bash
# Update talkplus setup times hourly
(cd /usr/share/cdr_stats/templates/frontend/comoyo; ./cdr-setup-times.py MONGODB-USERNAME MONGODB-PASSWORD >cdr-setup-times.log 2>&1)
----------------------------------------------
Replace mongdb-username and password with the apporpriate ones.
Add execute permissions:
 $ sudo chmod 755 /etc /etc/cron.hourly/cdr-hourly
Make cron restart config
 $ sudo kill -HUP `ps -lef | grep [c]rond`

